# devinity-api

NestJS API for Devinity. Scope: `DVN`.

## Structure

```
src/
  modules/           # Feature modules (user/, app.module.ts)
  db/                # Drizzle schemas
  env/env.ts         # Zod-validated env
  helpers/
test/                # e2e specs (vitest + supertest)
```

## Module pattern

Each feature under `src/modules/<feature>/`:

- `<feature>.module.ts` — imports, controllers, providers, exports
- `<feature>.controller.ts` — HTTP layer only
- `<feature>.service.ts` — business logic, DB, cache

Register new modules in `app.module.ts`.

## Database

- Drizzle ORM, schemas in `src/db/`
- Inject via `@Inject(DRIZZLE_DB)`
- Use `.returning()` on insert/update

## Auth

- Better-Auth via `@thallesp/nestjs-better-auth`
- CLI scripts: `auth:generate`, `auth:migrate` in package.json

## Shared types

- Import models/DTOs from `@repo/api` when shared with frontend
- External HTTP: prefer `httpClient` from `@repo/api/helpers` (see `http-client` rule)

## Testing

- Unit: Vitest (`vitest.config.ts`)
- E2e: `test/*.e2e-spec.ts` via `vitest.e2e.config.ts`, supertest + `AppModule`
- **Not Jest** — use `vitest` imports

## Scripts

- `pnpm dev` — nest start --watch
- `pnpm db:generate` / `db:migrate` — drizzle-kit
